    "name": "gatekeeper",
    "description": "**ASSIGNMENT DOCUMENTATION (Centralized Authentication & RBAC for Microservices**)\n\n**Gatekeeper** is a centralized Authentication and Authorization (AuthN/AuthZ) microservice designed to act as the security backbone of your application ecosystem. It implements a robust **Role-Based Access Control (RBAC)** architecture to ensure that every request is not only authenticated but also authorized based on granular permissions.\n\n### Key Features\n\n- **Dual-Token Security:** Utilizes **JWT (JSON Web Tokens)** with a short-lived `accessToken` for security and a long-lived `refreshToken` for seamless user sessions.\n    \n- **Granular RBAC:** Move beyond simple \"Admin\" or \"User\" labels. Gatekeeper allows you to define specific **Permissions** (e.g., `orders:read`, `users:delete`) and group them into **Roles**.\n    \n- **Audit Logging:** Every sensitive action (GET, POST, DELETE) is intercepted and logged with a timestamp, user ID, and status code, providing a full trail for security compliance.\n    \n- **Secure Cookie Handling:** Tokens are delivered via `httpOnly` and `Secure` cookies to mitigate XSS (Cross-Site Scripting) and CSRF (Cross-Site Request Forgery) risks.\n    \n- **Dynamic Role Assignment:** Administrators can promote or demote users in real-time without requiring a system reboot or manual database intervention.\n    \n\n### 🏗️ Technical Architecture\n\n1. **Identification:** The user logs in and receives a set of tokens from the auth service\n    \n2. **Verification:** For every protected request, middleware verifies the signature of the Bearer token.\n    \n3. **Authorization:** it checks if the user's assigned role contains the specific permission required for that route.\n    \n4. **Logging:** The interaction is recorded in the Audit Log database for monitoring.\n    \n\n### 🛠️ Tech Stack\n\n- **Runtime:** Node.js / Express.js\n    \n- **Database:** MongoDB (for storing Users, Roles, and Logs)\n    \n- **Auth:** JWT (jsonwebtoken)",
