          "description": "## RBAC & Permissions\n\nThese endpoints handle the configuration of roles and granular access control (RBAC).\n\n### 1\\. Create Permission\n\nDefines a new capability within the system for a specific resource.\n\n- **Method:** `POST`\n    \n- **Endpoint:** `/auth/permissions`\n    \n- JSON{ \"resource\": \"users\", \"action\": \"read\"}\n    \n- **Description:** Creates a permission string (e.g., `users:read`) that can later be attached to roles.\n    \n\n### 2\\. Get All Permissions\n\nRetrieves every permission currently defined in the database.\n\n- **Method:** `GET`\n    \n- **Endpoint:** `/auth/permissions`\n    \n- **Description:** Useful for populating dropdowns or lists in an Admin Dashboard.\n    \n\n### 3\\. Get All Roles\n\nLists all roles available in the system.\n\n- **Method:** `GET`\n    \n- **Endpoint:** `/auth/roles`\n    \n- **Description:** Fetches roles like `Admin`, `Editor`, or `Viewer` along with their associated metadata.\n    \n\n### 4\\. Assign Role to User\n\nLinks a specific role to a user account.\n\n- **Method:** `POST`\n    \n- **Endpoint:** `/auth/roles/assign/:userId`\n    \n- **Path Variable:** `userId` (The Unique ID of the target user)\n    \n- JSON{ \"roleId\": \"69df159d5fad50ca58e3a08c\"}\n    \n\n### 5\\. Remove Role from User\n\nRevokes a previously assigned role from a user.\n\n- **Method:** `POST`\n    \n- **Endpoint:** `/auth/roles/remove/:userId`\n    \n- **Path Variable:** `userId`\n    \n- JSON{ \"roleId\": \"69df159d5fad50ca58e3a08c\"}"
        },
